\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Investigating tool reports**\\n\\nI'm looking into the tool report regarding coverage, specifically using JaCoCo instruction coverage rather than a dynamic agent. I'm wondering if invoking MethodHandle via reflection affects how JaCoCo marks static call sites. If the classes for testing were loaded from the original jar instead of the instrumented one, that could complicate things. I also need to consider modifying existing tests instead of creating new ones, especially if the report indicates that tests weren’t recognized by Gradle.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring class naming issues**\\n\\nI'm considering whether the filename issue might be because it contains \\\"InnerArgsAndValue,\\\" while the rule suggests replacing `$` followed by a name with `Inner` and the name itself, like FooInnerBarTest. We thought we did this correctly. Maybe we need to adjust to using an underscore in the class name, as existing closure classes do. I'm also exploring whether invoking the class$ method is possible or if I might need to use `Class.forName` without direct reflection.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Clarifying static method invocation**\\n\\nI need to figure out if `InvokerHelper.invokeStaticMethod` calls the cached method directly. It seems like the issue is whether the method is public or not—since Groovy might only see public methods. If that’s the case, the test might fail if the method isn’t accessible. So, the next steps involve understanding the visibility of the method and confirming how it interacts with the caching mechanism. Let’s investigate this further.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_XKnv5H5BmWoD4pzS8J4sBA1K|fc_0b3a259b09eb7f87016a009b85b65c819492ae0a15bde447ad", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "rg \"class\\$\" /home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge8/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/source_context/io.rest-assured/rest-assured/5.5.0/main/extracted -n | head -2