[thinking] **Clarifying exceptions in testing**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I’m thinking about how a missing class triggers a ClassNotFoundException, leading to a NoClassDefFoundError. If I'm using Method.invoke, it wraps an InvocationTargetException, so that helps cover things. I can avoid using Class.forName directly in tests by utilizing reflection instead. Oh, and I have to make sure there’s no `$` in test class or file names, although strings can have them. It’s important!
[thinking] 
